Paper: hep-th/9409111

Date: 1994-09-19

Title: Is Supersymmetry Really Broken?

Authors: Edward Witten

Comments: 3 pages

Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A10 (1995) 1247-1248

In 2 + 1 dimensions, in the presence of gravity, supersymmetry can ensure thevanishing of the cosmological constant without requiring the equality of boseand fermi masses.